In a press conference, President Biden expressed his support for Ukraine in the face of Russian aggression. He condemned the atrocities committed by Russian forces and pledged to make Putin pay a heavy price. The United States, along with its allies and partners, is providing significant levels of security and humanitarian assistance to Ukraine. Biden announced an additional $800 million in security assistance, bringing the total to $1 billion for the week. This includes anti-aircraft systems, anti-armor systems, small arms, ammunition, drones, and other equipment. The United States is also mobilizing humanitarian relief and providing direct financial assistance to Ukraine's economy. Biden emphasized the importance of principles such as freedom and self-determination and stated that America stands with the forces of freedom. He signed a bill authorizing the drawdown of $800 million in defense articles. When asked about sending Polish MiGs to Ukraine, Biden declined to comment.